Class BoundedTimeInterval

  • java.lang.Object
    • ConcreteDomain.ConcreteObject
      • ConcreteDomain.SetObject
        • ConcreteDomain.SetTypes.BoundedTimeInterval
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataObject, java.io.Serializable

    public class BoundedTimeInterval
extends SetObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents time intervals like lecture time: every Monday between 10 and 12 o'clock, from 2016/10/15 until 2017/2/15

      • convexHull

        public java.time.LocalDateTime[] convexHull​()
        returns the isConvex hull of the bounded time intervals.
        As an example: consider the lecture time within a semster.
        The isConvex hull spans from the start of the first lecture until the end of the last lecture.
        Returns:
        the isConvex hull as [leftmost LocalDataTime, rightmost LocalDateTime]
